
# {{if .Service}}{{.Service.Name}}{{else}}Service{{end}} -- Rust Service Agent

## Overview

This agent manages a Rust service built with axum for HTTP/gRPC.
It handles scaffolding, building, testing, and deployment.

## Capabilities

- **HTTP server** with axum
- **gRPC server** with tonic (optional)
- **Hot-reload** during development via cargo-watch
- **Docker build** for production (multi-stage)
- **Kubernetes deployment** manifests

## File Layout

```
{{if .Service}}{{.Service.Name}}{{else}}service{{end}}/
  code/
    Cargo.toml
    src/
      main.rs          <- YOUR service entrypoint
```

## Common Operations

### Run locally

```bash
codefly run service
```

### Run tests

```bash
codefly test service
```

## Configuration

| Setting | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `hot-reload` | Enable file-watching hot reload via cargo-watch |
| `source-dir` | Directory containing Rust source (default: code) |
| `with-workspace` | Use cargo workspace mode |
